рном фонде DFJ Esprit в Лондоне. Ранее  руководил несколькими частными и корпоративными стартапами в сфере технологий, в том числе медицинским бизнес-подразделением United Corporation for Innovations. Начал свою карьеру в управлении активами, управляя фондом публичных рыночных технологий и телекоммуникаций. \\n",\n      "en": "Alex founded Target Global in 2012 and has been actively involved in building the organization ever since. He leads the firm’s growth-stage investment practice focusing primarily on consumer goods, FoodTech and healthcare. He has invested in many successful startups including Delivery Hero, Flo Health, Docplanner, and Amboss.<br><br>\\n \\n Prior to joining Target Global, Alex worked at the VC firm DFJ Esprit in London. Before that, he led several private and corporate startups in the tech field, including the medical business unit of United Corporation for Innovations. He started his career in asset management, running the public market tech & telco fund. \\n"\n    }\n  },\n\n  {\n    "img": "104.png",\n    "name": {\n      "ru": "Елена<br>Тофанюк ",\n      "en": "Elena  <br>Tofanyuk"\n    },\n    "position": {\n      "ru": "<b>модератор</b><br>первый заместитель<br> главного редактора<br>Forbes Russia",\n      "en": "<b>Moderator</b><br>First Deputy Editor-in-Chief, Forbes Russia"\n    },\n    "bio": {\n      "ru": "",\n      "en": ""\n    }\n  }\n]\n
